## Known Limitations

This is still representation pretraining infrastructure. It does not implement
the downstream MDN/forecast head.

The graph restore contract is declared and lossless by shape, but the current
Runtime report still exports flattened anchor-node samples. A later downstream
integration pass can decide when to publish a first-class `[B,N,C,De]`
representation artifact.

The report advertises leakage-proof fields, but Lattice remains the authority
for protected-split closure. This is intentional: Runtime writes evidence;
Lattice judges it.

Geometry is warning-only until empirical thresholds are calibrated on real
market pretraining runs.
